FBIS3-15400 "drsov044_h_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 Moldova 90 Percent Favor Independence LD0703111794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 7 Mar 94 LD0703111794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The majority of Moldova's people believe that the Republic should be an independent, united country, according to preliminary results of the nationwide survey of the population held on 6 March. Initial returns indicate that two-thirds of the Republic's registered electorate took part in the survey, INTERFAX reports. About 90 percent of those who voted gave an affirmative answer to the question of whether Moldova should develop as an independent, united, indivisible state.
